==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionVertexAtIntersection''' tool adds cosmetic vertex(es) at the intersection(s) of selected edges.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionVertexAtIntersectionExample.png|200px]]
{{Caption|On the right two added cosmetic vertexes}}

==Usage==

# Select two edges. Straight edges will be considered as infinite lines, and arcs will be considered as full circles.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionVertexAtIntersection.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw ExtensionVertexAtIntersection|Add Cosmetic Intersection Vertex(es)]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Centerlines/Threading → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionVertexAtIntersection.svg|16px]] Add Cosmetic Intersection Vertex(es)}} option from the menu.
# A cosmetic vertex is added at each intersection.


